# Downloading the Oracle VirtIO Drivers for Microsoft Windows
# Before you can install the Oracle VirtIO Drivers for Microsoft Windows you must download them from Oracle Software Delivery Cloud or My Oracle Support (MOS).

# To download the Oracle VirtIO Drivers for Microsoft Windows from Oracle Software Delivery Cloud:

# Navigate to https://edelivery.oracle.com and log in.

# Search for Oracle Linux.

# Select DLP: Oracle Linux 8.8.0.0.0 (Oracle Linux), or DLP: Oracle Linux 9.2.0.0.0 (Oracle Linux).

# Important:If you are using Oracle Linux 7, select either package.

# Click Continue.

# In the Platforms / Languages column, select Microsoft Windows x64 (64 bit) in the list and then click Continue.

# Review and accept the Oracle License Agreement and then click Continue.

# Click the file name that has the description: Oracle VirtIO Drivers for Microsoft Windows, Version 2.1.0, and save it to your system